<yield>6</yield>
<prepTime>PT30M</prepTime>
<cookTime>PT10M</cookTime>
<ingredient>850 gems minced pork </ingredient>
<ingredient>3 TBspoons olive oil </ingredient>
<ingredient>2 garlic cloves crushed</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 inch ginger grated</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/2 teaspoon chilli powder </ingredient>
<ingredient>1-2 limes juiced</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/3 cup fish sauce</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 teaspoon sugar</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/4 cup mint leaves chopped</ingredient>
<ingredient>3 cups rice noodles cooked and chopped</ingredient>
<ingredient>1 lettuce leaves removed</ingredient>
<ingredient>Extra limes to serve</ingredient>
<step>Prepare lettuce leaves and set aside. Google how to easily remove lettuce leaves easily.</step>
<step>Combine lime juice, fish sauce and sugar, stir to combine and set aside.</step>
<step>Heat oil in pan and cook meat until brown.</step>
<step>Add garlic, ginger and chilli and cook a few minutes.</step>
<step>Pour in juice mixture and stir through with noodles.</step>
<step>Serve inside a lettuce cup with lime on the side.</step>
<step>Alternately serve in rolled lettuce leaves, with thinly sliced cumber, lettuce and some chilli sauce.</step>
</recipe>

